				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned}&\text {Maximization of the net benefit}\\&\quad =\text {total revenue}\\&\qquad -\;\text {total costs of operation}\\&\qquad -\;\text {total costs of purchasing nutrients}\\&\qquad -\;\text {total costs of pipeline construction}\\&\qquad -\;\text {total inventory costs.} \end{aligned}$$\end{document}The second objective function minimizes the emission of greenhouse gases:Minimizes the emission of greenhouse gases=emission of carbon dioxide+emission of nitrous oxide+emission of methane.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
